content.text:
Here is what was going wrong and what we changed.

**Cause:** `useProfileChangeRequests` kept a local `version` in `useState` and only incremented it inside that hook instance when `persist` ran. The detail panel uses its own hook instance, so only that instance re-rendered. `OrganizationProfilePage` and `UserProfilePage` each call the hook separately and never saw that `version` bump, so their `useMemo(..., [requests])` stayed stale even though `localStorage` was updated.

**Fix:** Treat the persisted store as a single external source of truth:

1. **`storage.ts`** – After a successful `localStorage.setItem`, call `notifyProfileChangeRequestStoreListeners()`, which increments a module-level generation and notifies all subscribers. `subscribeProfileChangeRequestStore` registers listeners (and attaches a one-time `window.storage` listener so other tabs updating the same key also bump the generation).

2. **`use-profile-change-requests.ts`** – Replace local `version` state with `useSyncExternalStore(subscribeProfileChangeRequestStore, getProfileChangeRequestStoreGeneration, …)` and derive `requests` from `readProfileChangeRequestStore()` whenever that generation changes.

Any screen that uses `useProfileChangeRequests()` (user profile, organization profile, profile-change list, detail panel, etc.) now stays in sync after create / cancel / accept without edits to those pages.

